
[1]repand

   REPAND', a. [L. repandus.] In botany, a repand leaf is one, the rim of
   which is terminated by angles having sinuses between them, inscribed in
   the segment of a circle; or which has a bending or waved margin,
   without any angles; of which is bordered with numerous minute angles
   and small segments of circles alternately.
